name: 90 90 Hamstring
instructions: Lie on your back with hips and knees bent at 90 degrees
Place a strap or towel around one foot
Slowly extend the leg upward, keeping knee slightly bent
Feel the stretch in the hamstring without forcing
Hold for 20-30 seconds, then switch legs
modifications: Use a yoga strap or resistance band for better control
Keep bottom foot planted on wall for stability
Reduce range of motion if flexibility is limited
commonMistakes: Pulling too aggressively causing muscle strain

name: Ab Roller
instructions: Kneel on the floor and grip the ab roller handles
Engage your core and keep your back straight
Roll forward slowly, extending your body as far as comfortable
Roll back to starting position using your core muscles
modifications: Start from a wall or incline to reduce difficulty
Perform from knees instead of toes
Limit range of motion until core strength improves
commonMistakes: Not engaging core before rolling out
Going too far too fast causing form breakdown

name: All Fours Quad Stretch
instructions: Start on hands and knees in tabletop position
Reach back and grab one ankle with same-side hand
Hold stretch for 20-30 seconds, then switch sides
modifications: Use a strap if cannot reach ankle
commonMistakes: Allowing hips to rotate or tilt
Pulling too aggressively causing knee pain

name: Alternate Heel Touchers
instructions: Lie on back with knees bent, feet flat on floor
Lift shoulder blades off ground slightly
Reach right hand toward right heel by crunching obliques
Return to center and alternate to left side
modifications: Keep head on floor if neck strain occurs
Place hands on thighs instead of reaching to heels
commonMistakes: Using momentum instead of muscle control
Not engaging obliques, just moving arms

name: Alternate Incline Dumbbell Curl
instructions: Set bench to 30-45 degree incline and lie back with dumbbells
Start with both dumbbells at shoulder level, palms facing forward
Press one dumbbell up while keeping the other stable
Lower the pressed dumbbell back to starting position
Alternate arms for each rep, maintaining controlled tempo
modifications: Use lighter weights and perform both arms together
Decrease incline angle for less shoulder involvement
Use resistance bands instead of dumbbells
commonMistakes: Arching back excessively off the bench

name: Alternating Cable Shoulder Press
instructions: Stand between cable machines with D-handles at lowest setting
Cross cables in front of body, slight bend in elbows
Raise one arm out to side to shoulder height
Lower with control and alternate to other arm
modifications: Use lighter weight to perfect form
Reduce range of motion if shoulder discomfort
commonMistakes: Using momentum to swing weights up
Raising arms above shoulder height unnecessarily

name: Alternating Kettlebell Row
instructions: Start in bent-over position with kettlebell in one hand
Keep back flat and core engaged throughout
Pull kettlebell to hip, driving elbow back and up
Lower with control and alternate to other arm
modifications: Use lighter weight to master form first
Perform with hand supported on bench for stability
Row both arms together instead of alternating
commonMistakes: Using momentum instead of muscle control

name: Alternating Renegade Row
instructions: Start in plank position with hands on kettlebells or dumbbells
Feet wide for stability, core tight
Row one weight to hip while stabilizing with other arm
Lower with control and row opposite side
Keep hips level throughout - no rotation
modifications: Widen foot stance for more stability
Perform from knees instead of toes
Use hexagonal dumbbells to prevent rolling
commonMistakes: Allowing hips to rotate or sag
Using too heavy weight causing form breakdown

name: Ankle Circles
instructions: Sit or stand, lift one foot off ground
Draw large circles with toes, rotating ankle
modifications: Draw smaller circles if mobility limited
Use resistance band for added challenge
commonMistakes: Moving from knee instead of ankle
Making circles too small to be effective

name: Arnold Dumbbell Press
instructions: Sit on bench with back support, dumbbells at shoulder height
Start with palms facing you, elbows forward
As you press up, rotate palms to face forward
Reverse the rotation on the way down
modifications: Use lighter weights to master rotation
Reduce range of motion if shoulder mobility limited
commonMistakes: Not rotating palms fully during press
Using too much weight causing poor form

name: Axle Deadlift
instructions: Stand with feet hip-width apart, axle bar over midfoot
Grip the thicker axle bar firmly, challenging grip strength
Keep chest up, back flat, engage lats
Drive through heels, extending hips and knees simultaneously
Lower with control, maintaining neutral spine
modifications: Use straps to reduce grip demand
Start with lighter weight than regular deadlift
Perform from elevated blocks to reduce range
commonMistakes: Letting bar drift away from body

name: Back Flyes With Bands
instructions: Lie face up on bench with dumbbells extended above chest
Slight bend in elbows, palms facing each other
Lower weights out to sides in wide arc
Feel stretch across chest at bottom
Squeeze chest to bring weights back together
modifications: Perform on incline for upper chest emphasis
commonMistakes: Bending elbows too much (turns into press)
Dropping weights too low causing shoulder strain
Not maintaining slight elbow bend throughout

name: Band Assisted Pull Up
instructions: Loop resistance band over pull-up bar
Place knee or foot in band for assistance
Grip bar slightly wider than shoulder width
Pull body up until chin clears bar
Lower with control back to full hang
modifications: Use thicker band for more assistance
Perform negative-only reps (jump up, lower slowly)
commonMistakes: Not achieving full range of motion
Shrugging shoulders instead of pulling with lats

name: Barbell Ab Rollout
instructions: Load barbell with plates and kneel behind it
Grip barbell with hands shoulder-width apart
Engage core and maintain neutral spine
Roll barbell forward, extending body while keeping core tight
Pull back to starting position using core muscles
modifications: Perform from knees instead of toes
Use a wall to limit forward distance
Start with partial range of motion
commonMistakes: Not bracing core before rolling out
Going too far causing form collapse

name: Barbell Ab Rollout On Knees
instructions: Load barbell with plates and kneel behind it
Grip barbell with hands shoulder-width apart
Engage core and maintain neutral spine
Roll barbell forward, extending body while keeping core tight
Pull back to starting position using core muscles
modifications: Perform from knees instead of toes
Use a wall to limit forward distance
Start with partial range of motion
commonMistakes: Not bracing core before rolling out
Going too far causing form collapse

instructions: Step onto the treadmill and start at a walking pace
Gradually increase speed to desired running/walking pace
Maintain proper posture with relaxed shoulders
Land mid-foot and keep stride natural
Cool down by gradually reducing speed

name: Dumbbell Press
instructions: Lie on flat bench with dumbbells at shoulder level
Press dumbbells up until arms are fully extended
Lower dumbbells with control to chest level
modifications: Perform on incline bench for upper chest focus
Single arm variation for core engagement
commonMistakes: Not bringing dumbbells to full depth

name: Bent Over Row
instructions: Bend at hips with barbell in hands, back flat
Pull barbell to lower chest/upper abdomen
Squeeze shoulder blades together at top
Lower with control to starting position
modifications: Use resistance bands instead of weights
Single arm variation for better focus
commonMistakes: Using momentum instead of controlled movement
Not pulling elbows back far enough

name: Stationary Bike
instructions: Adjust seat so knee has slight bend at bottom of pedal stroke
Start with light resistance and gradually increase
commonMistakes: Pedaling with toes instead of full foot

name: Push Up
instructions: Start in plank position with hands shoulder-width apart
Lower body until chest nearly touches ground
Push back up to starting position
Maintain straight line from head to heels

name: Lat Pulldown
instructions: Sit at lat pulldown machine with knees secured
Grip bar slightly wider than shoulder width
Pull bar down to upper chest
Return to starting position with control
modifications: Vary grip width for different emphasis

name: Rowing Machine
instructions: Sit on rower with feet secured, knees bent
Drive with legs first, then pull with arms
Reverse the motion: arms, body, then legs

name: Shoulder Press
instructions: Stand or sit with dumbbells at shoulder height
Press weights overhead until arms fully extended
Lower weights with control to shoulder level

name: Bicep Curl
instructions: Stand with dumbbells at sides, palms facing forward
Curl weights up keeping elbows stationary
Squeeze biceps at top of movement

name: Tricep Extension
instructions: Hold dumbbell behind head with both hands
Extend arms overhead while keeping elbows stable
Lower weight behind head with control

name: Hamstring Stretch
instructions: Sit on floor with one leg extended
Reach toward toes with both hands
Keep back straight, hinge at hips

name: Quad Stretch
instructions: Stand on one leg, grab opposite ankle behind you

name: Burpees
instructions: Start standing, drop into squat position
Place hands on floor and jump feet back to plank
Jump feet back to squat position
Explosively jump up with arms overhead

name: Lateral Raise
instructions: Raise arms out to sides to shoulder height
